# CARES monorepo context

Before implementing or refactoring, **read applicable rules** in `.cursor/rules/`:

| Area | Rule file | When |
|------|-----------|------|
| Flutter mobile | `mobile-flutter.mdc` | Any work under `mobile/` |
| NestJS server | `server-nestjs.mdc` | Any work under `server/` |

For Cursor product behavior (rules, agents, skills, hooks), use official docs: https://docs.cursor.com

## Repo layout

- `mobile/` — Flutter app; **snake_case** files/folders (see `mobile-flutter.mdc`)
- `server/` — NestJS API; **kebab-case** files (see `server-nestjs.mdc`)
- `docker-compose.yaml` — local infra

## Global expectations

- Minimize scope; match existing conventions in the touched area.
- Do not commit secrets (`.env`, keys, tokens).
- Only create git commits when the user explicitly asks.
